March 29 at 2:36 PM ·

SCHOOL MEAL LOCATIONS – TUOLUMNE COUNTY (MAR 30 – APR 3)
All districts are providing some kind of meal assistance and all schools are operating under a waiver that allows them to serve any child under the age of 18 or students enrolled in the Transition program. PATHS - Parents At Twain Harte School
July 29, 2018 at 6:27 AM ·

Have you signed up for Amazon Smile, and selected PATHS as the non profit you’d like to benefit? It is so simple! Follow this link and select PATHS, then each time you shop Amazon, remember to log in through Amazon Smile. Simple instructions to set up an app button for your phone are in the photo below.

In a week, I have earned $2.05 for our school, just by doing my regular shopping! If all of our families signed up, funds would add up quickly! All funds raised go directly toward buying books, educational supplies (expo markers, homework folders, pencils, glue sticks,etc.), field trips, scholarships, and paying for events that your students benefit from every day.

Thank you for your support!

shared_text:
Tuolumne County Sheriff
March 9, 2018 at 3:08 PM ·

UPDATE: 2:23 pm
Lockdown of Twain Harte Elementary has been lifted. Male subject is confirmed no longer on campus.

2:10 pm
TWAIN HARTE ELEMENTARY school on lockdown, NOT Curtis Creek. Sorry for the confusion!

Deputies will remain on scene to make sure the children are safe, we believe the male subject is off the campus at this time.

Original Post:
Approximately 25 minutes ago, a traffic stop was made near Twain Harte Elementary, involving two males. One male was arrested, as the other male (white male, heavy set, blue jeans, dark blue shirt) fled on foot. Deputies are on scene and searching the area. The school was placed on lockdown as a precaution while we investigate and search.

post_text: Please be advised that this morning at 7:05 a.m. a 7th grade student was approached by a white male in a white van asking for “help with something in the back of his van.” The student ran into the woods to hide before continuing to the bus stop. This took place near Conte Court in Mi Wuk Village. The driver had a hoodie on with a ski mask that coveted part of his face. The van was white without windows on the side and no type of advertising. The Sheriff’s Department was dispatched and a report was made. Please remind your students to beware of any strangers approaching them in a suspicious manner and to report any type of situation to their bus driver, school personnel or parent.
